<div id="review_2349632904" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2349632904" />
    <a title="Allison" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27047099-allison"><img alt="Allison" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1450468223p2/27047099.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2349632904?book_show_action=true">Apr 03, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Allison" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Allison" href="/user/show/27047099-allison">Allison</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27047099-allison?shelf=canadian-native-issues">canadian-native-issues</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27047099-allison?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27047099-allison?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/27047099-allison?shelf=2019-bingo">2019-bingo</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2349632904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2893432188903554190">I really do, and always have, liked the style of Thomas King&apos;s writing, and this is no exception. It&apos;s engaging and intelligent each time. <br/><br/>This book reads very much like a text book -- and come to think of it, would work very well as one for a high school class. Why isn&apos;t it used that way? We&apos;d all be well-served to learn about this stuff in our early years, and this is an accessible volume for exactly that. <br/><br/>It&apos;s pages and pages and pages of the same: of the embarrassing and downright shaming st</span>
  <span id="freeText2893432188903554190" style="display:none">I really do, and always have, liked the style of Thomas King's writing, and this is no exception. It's engaging and intelligent each time. <br /><br />This book reads very much like a text book -- and come to think of it, would work very well as one for a high school class. Why isn't it used that way? We'd all be well-served to learn about this stuff in our early years, and this is an accessible volume for exactly that. <br /><br />It's pages and pages and pages of the same: of the embarrassing and downright shaming stuff we have done to North America's native peoples over the centuries. It's nearly impossible to believe. Why are we always such ASSES??? Honestly?! <br /><br />I happen to be concurrently reading <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9981818.The_Chimps_of_Fauna_Sanctuary_A_True_Story_of_Resilience_and_Recovery" title="The Chimps of Fauna Sanctuary A True Story of Resilience and Recovery by Andrew Westoll" rel="nofollow noopener">The Chimps of Fauna Sanctuary: A True Story of Resilience and Recovery</a>, a totally different story about another way that we humans are jerks. Why do we keep doing this?? Why can't we just stop and play nice?? Why???? <br /><br />I wish I could do something. I think this every time I read more about how Canada's/N. America's native populations have been ill-treated (to put it lightly). I don't know what to do, and I'm ashamed of our history. There are no answers given in this book (or any that I've read). However, I did like King's very practical and succinct ending to this book. He's a smart, impressive man. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2893432188903554190" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


